-- U.K. Pound Rises as BOE’s Posen Ends Push for Further Stimulus
-- B y   P a u l   D o b s o n
-- 2012-04-18T08:36:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-18/u-k-pound-rises-as-boe-s-posen-ends-push-for-further-stimulus.html
The pound climbed to its strongest
level against the euro since 2010 and rose against the dollar
after minutes showed the Bank of England’s  Adam Posen  ended his
push for further stimulus.  Sterling appreciated 0.4 percent to 82.08 pence per euro at
9:34 a.m. London time after gaining as much as 0.5 percent to
82.05 pence, the strongest level since September 2010.  The U.K. currency rose 0.3 percent to $1.5968.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Dobson in London at 
